 of the parameters between the watch and actigraphy were considerably higher than those of the ring. The watch also showed a significant difference in TST (P\&lt;.001) between female and male groups. Conclusions: In a sample population of healthy adults, the sleep parameters of both the Oura ring and Samsung watch have acceptable mean differences and indicate significant correlations with actigraphy, but the ring outperforms the watch in terms of the nonstaging sleep parameters.},
